The paper deals with a network coding problem, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The problem involves finding an optimal encoding scheme, which can be formulated as a linear program and falls under the category of optimization (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a new definition of the local partial clique cover, which is a graph-theoretic concept and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents a construction for generalized interlinked cycle graphs, which is a topic in graph theory and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
